It stated that mercantilism and protectionism have different aims, which is simply not true. They DO have different processes, respectively different ways, how to reach the same goal. Mercantilism is an ideology while protectionism is a policy. Robert Gilpin even states that Protectionism is a policy within mercantilism. Unfortunately i only found the powerpointpresentation, i do not remember the book where he states that... so my source is missing for the changes i made.
